      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_600750ee103649c1b5d99fdc2a469f0c\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v2.0\",\n      \"title\": \"Repairability Scoring Rubric v2.0 iFixit https://www.ifixit.com › Wiki › Repairability_Scoring_...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* Edit\\n* Options\\n\\n* History\\n\\n# Repairability Scoring Rubric v2.0\\n\\nHere you'll find a summary of the various criteria iFixit considers when calculating repairability scores under scorecard version 2.0.\\n\\n**Scoring Factors**\\n\\n| |Weight |Note |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n|Design for Repair |80% |_Ease of disassembly/reassembly_ |\\n|Service Manual (if any) |10% |_Free, public, complete, available via OEM support site_ |\\n|Parts Availability & Cost |10% |_Only OEM parts considered_ |\\n|Unique Product Identifier |N/A |_Gating function for full credit on service manual, parts availability_ |\\n|Parts Pairing |N/A |_Penalty only, global, up to -100%_ |\\n\\n**Factors Not Considered**\\n\\n|Software Updates |_Duration of software security updates is slated for inclusion in a future version of the scorecard._ |\\n| --- | --- |\\n|Other |_[Reserved]_ |\\n\\n**Revisions from v1.9**\\n\\n|Tools and Scaling Factors |_Added new tools and adjusted tool categorizations and scaling factors._ |\\n| --- | --- |\\n|Proxy Times |_Removed/replaced deprecated actions and prioritized actions and proxy times associated with specific hardware design features._ |\\n|Scoring Definitions and Guidance |_Refined internal definitions and guidance for numerous scoring criteria for greater consistency and ease of use._ |\\n\\n**Summary of Revisions**\\n\\nBlock Image\\n\\n**Reference**\\n\\n* [How iFixit Scores Repairability](https://www.ifixit.com/News/75533/how-ifixit-scores-repairability)\\n* Provisional Scoring Explained\\n* [Smartphone Repairability Index](https://www.ifixit.com/smartphone-repairability)\\n\\n### Author\\n\\n#### Jeff Suovanen\\n\\nMember since: 08/06/13\\n\\n453,173 Reputation\\n\\n259 Guides authored\\n\\nBadges: 49\\n\\n* \\n* \\n* \\n\\n\\\\+46 more badges\\n\\n### Team\\n\\n#### iFixit Member of iFixit\\n\\nStaff\\n\\n122 Members\\n\\n26,591 Guides authored\\n\\n### 1 Comment\\n\\nAdd Comment\\n\\nSlaqe diwr fksjawo f\\n\\nsalad11223300@gmail.com \\\\- Mar 5, 2026 Reply Share\\n\\n#### Add Comment\\n\\nCancel Post comment\\n\\n**View Statistics:**\\n\\nPast 24 Hours: 6\\n\\nPast 7 Days: 59\\nPast 30 Days: 206\\n\\nAll Time: 3,710\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/repairability\",\n      \"title\": \"Repairability - iFixit\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# Repairable Products Make Good Sense\\n\\n# **Repair is good for people, the planet, and product longevity** .\\n\\n# We rate products to make it easier to buy repairable devices.\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/smartphone-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Smartphones\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/smartphone-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/tablet-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Tablets\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/tablet-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/laptop-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Laptops\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/laptop-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/wireless-earbud-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Wireless Earbuds\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/wireless-earbud-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/e-reader-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# E-readers\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.\\ncom/repairability/e-reader-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/smartwatch-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Smartwatches\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/smartwatch-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/mini-pc-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Mini PCs\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/mini-pc-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/handheld-game-console-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Handheld Game Consoles\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/handheld-game-console-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/wireless-headphones-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Wireless Headphones\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/wireless-headphones-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# What is Repairability?\\n\\nRepairability means making it possible—and ideally easy—to repair a product.\\n\\n...\\n\\nSometimes manufacturers use proprietary screws, requiring drivers only available to their own repair techs—like [Apple’s pentalobe](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.ifixit.com/News/14279/apples-diabolical-plan-to-screw-your-iphone&sa=D&source=docs&ust=1688079314464072&usg=AOvVaw1MgEO3FWV2zWj3O5mpaA-A) and [Jura’s oval](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.jura-parts.com/Jura-Oval-Head-Repair-Tool-p/10542.htm&sa=D&source=docs&ust=1688079314464146&usg=AOvVaw0wsU2MbF6sxJAGmNEuYimd) . Sometimes designers make opening a product destructive. The original [Microsoft Surface laptop](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.ifixit.com/Teardown/Microsoft%2BSurface%2BLaptop%2BTeardown/92915&sa=D&source=docs&ust=1688079314465147&usg=AOvVaw3zIIBR3maUwYrLX_Dpw8as) had a felt case that had to be cut open and spot welds underneath that (newer models are much better!).\\n\\n# Missing access to parts, tools, and documentation\\nRepairability isn’t just about design—it’s about the whole ecosystem. If people can’t get access to parts, tools, documentation, or software, they can’t finish a repair. A [study of repair behavior](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://scholar.google.com/scholar_url?url%3Dhttps://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/am/pii/S0921344916300349%26hl%3Den%26sa%3DT%26oi%3Ducasa%26ct%3Dufr%26ei%3Dd9yUZMPdF8eP6rQPsbqOqAE%26scisig%3DAGlGAw86wBmmpjOuSFPcoVAEJmIm&sa=D&source=docs&ust=1688079314467909&usg=AOvVaw3qi6CR_fGcaPqic4YakPJ9) named the unavailability of parts, tools, and manuals as three of the main reasons for unsuccessful repairs.\\n\\n# Parts pairing\\n\\nEven if a product can physically be repaired, too many products have additional [software barriers to repair](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.ifixit.com/News/69320/how-parts-pairing-kills-independent-repair&sa=D&source=docs&ust=1688079314469857&usg=AOvVaw2QbfDexlHdmh4_JzWxtqEB) .\\nNearly half of iPhone parts today are paired, meaning that you need special manufacturer-only software to repair them without errors. A truly repairable product doesn’t have software limitations like this.\\n\\n# There’s a better way.\\n\\niFixit is working on both sides of the table, supporting  \\nlegislation to enforce Right to Repair initiatives and help  \\n[manufacturers make repairable products](https://www.ifixit.com/services) .\\n\\n# Learn More\\n\\n* Who fixes stuff? Find out more about the [iFixit community](https://www.ifixit.com/Community) .\\n* Like documentaries? Want to hear more about planned obsolescence? Check out [The Light Bulb Conspiracy](http://topdocumentaryfilms.com/light-bulb-conspiracy/) .\\n* Explore the [iFixit blog](https://www.ifixit.com/News/75533/how-ifixit-scores-repairability) for repair stories and news.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v1.1\",\n      \"title\": \"Repairability Scoring Rubric v1.1 iFixit · https://www.ifixit.com › Wiki › Repairability_Scoring_Ru...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* Edit\\n* Options\\n\\n* History\\n\\n# Repairability Scoring Rubric v1.1\\n\\nHere you'll find a summary of the various criteria considered when calculating iFixit repairability scores under scorecard version 1.1.\\n\\n**Scoring Factors**\\n\\n| |Weight |Note |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n|Design for Repair |90% |_Ease of disassembly/reassembly_ |\\n|Service Manual (if any) |10% |_Free, public, available via OEM support site_ |\\n\\n**Factors Not Considered**\\n\\n|Parts Availability |_Replacement parts available for purchase from the OEM at reasonable cost to end users will be a requirement in a future scorecard update._ |\\n| --- | --- |\\n|Parts Pairing |_Where common repairs are inhibited by parts pairing or calibration issues (e.g. full or partial loss of function, authenticity warnings, etc.) for which the OEM provides no freely available software-based remedy, penalties may be included in a future version of the scoring model._ |\\n|Unique Product Identifier |_In a future scorecard update, maximum points may be reserved for devices which can be readily identified (model number, service tag, etc.) in a non-working condition, making it straightforward to find compatible parts and instructions._ |\\n|Software Updates |_Duration of software updates may be included in a future version of the scorecard._ |\\n\\n**Revisions from v1.0**\\n\\n|Reassembly |_Added proxy times for various reassembly actions and design features. Over-reliance on adhesives is now directly penalized due to added time for cleaning, prepping, and bonding, the need for additional tools/fixtures, the need for consumables/supplies, and increased possibility of user frustration/error. Devices that use adhesives but can be reliably re-assembled by other means (i.e. reusable fasteners) receive a reduced penalty._ |\\n| --- | --- |\\n\\n**Summary of Revisions**\\n\\nBlock Image\\n\\n**Reference**\\n\\n* [How iFixit Scores Repairability](https://www.ifixit.\\ncom/News/75533/how-ifixit-scores-repairability)\\n* Provisional Scoring Explained\\n* [Smartphone Repairability Index](https://www.ifixit.com/smartphone-repairability)\\n\\n### Author\\n\\n#### Jeff Suovanen\\n\\nMember since: 08/06/13\\n\\n453,173 Reputation\\n\\n259 Guides authored\\n\\nBadges: 49\\n\\n* \\n* \\n* \\n\\n\\\\+46 more badges\\n\\n### Team\\n\\n#### iFixit Member of iFixit\\n\\nStaff\\n\\n122 Members\\n\\n26,591 Guides authored\\n\\n### 0 Comments\\n\\nAdd Comment\\n\\n#### Add Comment\\n\\nCancel Post comment\\n\\n**View Statistics:**\\n\\nPast 24 Hours: 2\\n\\nPast 7 Days: 6\\n\\nPast 30 Days: 19\\n\\nAll Time: 809\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.notebookcheck.net/5700HQ-vs-i5-7300HQ-vs-m3-7Y30_6829_8417_8163.247596.0.html\",\n      \"title\": \"Intel Core i7-5700HQ vs Intel Core i5-7300HQ vs ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Intel Core i7-5700HQ vs Intel Core i5-7300HQ vs ...\\nCompared to the faster Core i7 models, the Core i5 does not support Hyper Threading and has lower clocks. The CPU cores run at 2.5 - 3.5 GHz (4 cores up to 3.1,\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/laptop-repairability-scores\",\n      \"title\": \"Laptop Repairability Scores | Most Repairable Laptops - iFixit\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# Laptop Repairability Scores\\n\\nJump to Scores\\n\\n# You have the right to repair the things you own—but how easily can that be done?\\n\\nTo find out, our engineers tear down the latest laptops and score their repairability from zero (unrepairable) to ten (easiest to repair) so you can pick a product that is easy to repair and lasts as long as possible.\\n\\n# What makes a repairable device?\\n\\nIt should be straightforward to disassemble and replace whatever’s broken, using parts and instructions supplied (or endorsed) by the manufacturer. But that’s just to start—repairability means so much more. For full details, see our [repairability scoring explainer](https://www.ifixit.com/News/75533/how-ifixit-scores-repairability) .\\n\\n# Repairability is a moving target\\n\\nWe update our scoring rubric frequently to stay current with new technologies, materials, and design trends.\\nThis means that devices scored in years past might not fare exactly the same if they were re-scored today, but they can be readily compared with their contemporaries. For a precise list of criteria used to calculate each score, click the scorecard version number linked to each device below. For a downloadable (CSV) list of all scores, [click here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1R_egXm7iwR0isCt_UxcGtheFEwLj9SNhxC5DWnAqKIc/edit=0) .\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n# Laptop Scores\\n\\nSorted by newest to oldest\\n\\n# Lenovo ThinkPad T14 Gen 7 and T16 Gen 5\\n\\n2026\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Storage and memory are readily repairable/upgradeable using industry-standard parts.\\n* The battery is easily replaced, and the keyboard replacement procedure is best-in-class.\\n* Overall very high modularity, including individually replaceable Thunderbolt ports.\\n* Lenovo provides thorough repair instructions and sells replacement parts.\\n\\n[Scorecard v2.2](https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v2.2)\\n# MacBook Pro 14-inch (M5, 2025)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/MacBook_Pro_14%22_2025_%28M5%29)\\n\\n2025\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Battery replacements are do-able (if not exactly easy).\\n* The Thunderbolt port design is highly modular and repair-friendly.\\n* Apple offers a full service manual and a good selection of replacement parts for end users.\\n\\n###### CONS\\n\\n* Storage is not removable or serviceable, the keyboard is riveted down, and pentalobe screws bar the way for all repairs.\\n\\n[Scorecard v2.2](https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v2.2)\\n\\n# Lenovo ThinkPad P16 Gen 3\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Lenovo_ThinkPad_P16_Gen_3)\\n\\n2025\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Storage and memory are readily repairable/upgradeable using industry-standard parts.\\n* The battery is easily replaced, and the keyboard replacement procedure is best-in-class.\\n* Lenovo typically provides thorough support for P-series repairs (instructions and replacement parts).\\n\\n###### CONS\\n\\n...\\n\\n* The battery is easily replaced, and the keyboard replacement procedure is best-in-class.\\n* Overall high modularity, apart from a handful of soldered ports and a bundled fan/heat sink assembly.\\n\\n[Scorecard v1.9](https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v1.9)  \\n**[Learn More](https://www.ifixit.com/Document/sunTY6dbbJvOMRjP/Repairability-Snapshot-%E2%80%93-Lenovo-ThinkPad-T14-Gen-5.pdf)**\\n\\n# Framework Laptop 16\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Framework_Laptop_16%22)\\n\\n2023\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Repairability is strongly prioritized in the design from top to bottom.\\n* Virtually all major components are modular and readily replaceable, including the graphics module.\\n* Framework typically offers a factory service manual and a robust selection of replacement parts for end users.\\n\\n[Scorecard v1.7](https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v1.7)  \\n**[Learn More](https://www.ifixit.com/Document/ZdWVvQ2AHp5MDYgO/Repairability-Snapshot---Framework-Laptop-16.pdf)**\\n\\n...\\n\\nifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v1.3)  \\n**[Learn More](https://www.ifixit.com/News/54122/macbook-pro-2021-teardown)**\\n\\n[View Legacy Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/legacy-laptop-scores)\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.notebookcheck.net/i5-7300HQ-vs-5700HQ-vs-5750HQ_8417_6829_6830.247596.0.html\",\n      \"title\": \"Intel Core i5-7300HQ vs Intel Core i7-5700HQ vs ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Intel Core i5-7300HQ vs Intel Core i7-5700HQ vs ...\\nCompared to the faster Core i7 models, the Core i5 does not support Hyper Threading and has lower clocks. The CPU cores run at 2.5 - 3.5 GHz (4 cores up to 3.1,\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/News/category/repairability-en\",\n      \"title\": \"Category: Repairability\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-05-27\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Category: Repairability\\nMay 27, 2026. by Sandra Hiller - iFixit. Tech News · We're Now Scoring ... Lenovo's New ThinkPads Score 10/10 for Repairability . Editorial Note: We have\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/News/115827/new-thinkpads-score-perfect-10-repairability\",\n      \"title\": \"Lenovo’s New T-Series ThinkPads Score 10/10 for Repairability - iFixit\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-07-03\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"com/News/75533/how-ifixit-scores-repairability) (repairable design and availability of parts, tools, and information) and does not reward working with us over other ways of getting repair materials to customers._\\n\\nThere are “repairable” laptops, and then there are _ThinkPad T-series_ laptops: the ones corporate IT buys by the pallet, images by the thousands, and expects to survive years of all-day use. During their lives they’ll weather countless commutes, on-the-go presentations, and inevitable splashes of coffee.\\n\\nThat’s why Lenovo’s newest ThinkPads are such a big deal: the new **[T14 Gen 7](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Lenovo_ThinkPad_T14_Gen_7)** and **T16 Gen 5** score an eye-popping **10 out of 10** on our [repairability scale](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability) . It’s the first time the T-series has ever earned our top rating. ( _The score is [provisional](https://www.ifixit.\\ncom/Wiki/Provisional_Repairability_Scores) , for now—we’ll finalize it when official parts and instructions become available through [Lenovo’s support site](https://pcsupport.lenovo.com/) , which we fully expect will happen in the near future._ )\\n\\nThis moves past repairability as a niche feature for tinkerers. This is repairability showing up in the machine that practically defines the mainstream business laptop category.\\n\\nA technician lifts the back cover off of the new ThinkPad T14 laptop _Come on in, the repairability is fine_ . _No, really—getting inside these new ThinkPads is a breeze._\\n\\n## **Pushing Beyond Greatness**\\n\\nRepairability at this level doesn’t happen overnight.\\n\\nTwo years ago at [**MWC 2024**](https://www.ifixit.com/News/95395/ifixit-and-lenovo-work-together-to-make-laptop-repairability-the-standard-en) , Lenovo introduced a repairability-focused generation of ThinkPad T14 laptops that scored an already-phenomenal **9/10** . Our [Solutions team](https://www.ifixit.\\n\\n...\\n\\nWe addressed this by bringing design, engineering, service, quality, and sustainability together from day one.”\\n\\n[](https://valkyrie.cdn.ifixit.com/media/2026/03/02154516/lpcamm2_3x2.jpg) [](https://valkyrie.cdn.ifixit.com/media/2026/03/02154520/ssd_3x2.jpg) _Modular [LPCAMM2](https://www.ifixit.com/News/95078/lpcamm2-memory-is-finally-here) memory makes a triumphant return, along with standard M.2 SSD storage._\\n\\nFrom our perspective, the results speak for themselves. The new T-Series repair ecosystem is built around accessible, replaceable parts:\\n\\n* An easily swapped battery with a nearly tool-free procedure\\n* Industry standard M.2 SSD storage\\n* One of the easiest keyboard replacement procedures we’ve ever seen\\n* LPCAMM2 memory that’s fast, efficient, _and_ [easily serviced](https://www.ifixit.com/News/95078/lpcamm2-memory-is-finally-here)\\n* Streamlined display repairs\\n* A modular cooling system, with an independently replaceable fan\\n* Fully modular Thunderbolt ports\\nAll of that is soon to be backed by official, publicly available repair documentation and a replacement parts pipeline designed for real-world service. _Bravo_ , Lenovo.\\n\\n[](https://valkyrie.cdn.ifixit.com/media/2026/03/02154506/battery_con_3x2.jpg) [](https://valkyrie.cdn.ifixit.com/media/2026/03/02154509/fan_3x2.jpg) [](https://valkyrie.cdn.ifixit.com/media/2026/03/02154507/driver_3x2.jpg) _Easy access to the battery and a modular cooling system help round out the new T-Series repairability scores._\\n\\n## **10/10 is Not the End**\\n\\n10/10 is the highest repairability score we award, and the new T-series earns it.\\n\\nThat said, there are _always_ ways to improve: making repairs faster, simpler, more forgiving, with fewer tool requirements and more components that can be swapped without escalating into a major teardown.\\n\\nRemoving the modular Thunderbolt ports from inside a Thinkpad T14 Gen 7 _One of the biggest repairability wins: fully modular, individually replaceable Thunderbolt ports._\\nFor example, Lenovo made the high-wear USB-C/Thunderbolt-side of things meaningfully better by going modular where it matters most. That alone is a huge win. But not every port on this machine gets the same fully modular treatment yet—some of the lesser-used I/O still lives on the main board or on a smaller breakout board, rather than being a quick-swap module on its own.\\n\\nWe noted a similar lack of modularity on the Wi-Fi module, where repairs or upgrades will be impractical at best. And while whole display assembly replacements are thankfully straightforward, there’s still a bit of adhesive to navigate if you want to drill into the display itself for a panel swap or a webcam repair.\\n\\nThese are \"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/News/95395/ifixit-and-lenovo-work-together-to-make-laptop-repairability-the-standard-en\",\n      \"title\": \"iFixit and Lenovo Work Together to Make Laptop Repairability the Standard\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-06-30\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Free Shipping on Domestic Orders $75+\\n\\niFixit\\n\\n# iFixit and Lenovo Work Together to Make Laptop Repairability the Standard\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/User/4158147/Manuel+Haeussermann)\\n\\nArticle by: [Manuel Haeussermann](https://www.ifixit.com/User/4158147/Manuel+Haeussermann) [@mhaeussermann](https://www.ifixit.com/User/4158147/Manuel+Haeussermann)\\n\\n* February 24, 2024\\n* Filed under: iFixit , Site News\\n* 1 Comment\\n\\nShare\\n\\nBig changes need strong allies. That’s why over the past several years, we’ve been working to help manufacturers [join the fight for repair](https://www.ifixit.com/News/58484/manufacturers-are-joining-the-fight-for-repair) . More and more, they see repairability not just as an economic advantage, but also as a way to differentiate their products and [build brand loyalty](https://www.ifixit.com/News/76806/fixing-to-be-an-iconic-brand-how-repair-ecosystems-build-brand-loyalty) . People like products that last, it turns out.\\nWhen it comes to laptops, Lenovo’s [ThinkPads](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Lenovo_Thinkpad) have been known for durability for decades, so much so that [they have been in use in low Earth orbit](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RmqPfLWe8G0) , a place without onsite service technicians.\\n\\nWith the help of iFixit, Lenovo is taking the repairability of its ThinkPad T14 model to the next level.\\n\\nThe ThinkPad T14 Gen 5 prioritizes easy replacement of key components like the battery, SSD, RAM, and the display assembly.\\n\\nDuring the development process, our Solutions team—comprised of repairability experts and tech writers—disassembled, documented, and evaluated the internal design of the laptop to provide feedback. Lenovo’s design team engaged with this feedback. They listened to what we had to say about the repairability of their laptop.\\nThe result: A ThinkPad that looks deceptively similar to its predecessors from the outside, but features a drastic repairability improvement on the inside.\\n\\nWhat does this mean? While the [ThinkPad T14 Gen 3](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Lenovo_ThinkPad_T14_Gen_3) earned a decent 7 out of 10 on our Repairability Scoring Rubric and a shoutout for an impressive keyboard replacement procedure, the Solutions team saw some clear room for improvements, e.g. the soldered-in RAM.\\n\\nBased on our feedback, Lenovo made changes to the internals that brought the score of the [ThinkPad T14 Gen 5](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Lenovo_ThinkPad_T14_Gen_5) to an astounding [9 out of 10](https://www.ifixit.com/Document/sunTY6dbbJvOMRjP/Repairability-Snapshot-%E2%80%93-Lenovo-ThinkPad-T14-Gen-5.pdf?referrer=wiki:547636) . From easily replaceable parts, to a design that supports safe and straightforward repairs, Lenovo’s team prioritized repair down the cable connections and fasteners.\\nConsidering Lenovo is the [largest PC vendor worldwide](https://www.gartner.com/en/newsroom/press-releases/2023-01-11-gartner-says-worldwide-pc-shipments-declined-28-percent-in-fourth-quarter-of-2022-and-16-percent-for-the-year) , this is no small feat. With this new laptop, they bring repairability to their best-selling business laptop. And that’s not the only thing they did when it comes to repairability. Just last year, Lenovo Executive Luca Rossi laid out the company’s goal to have 84% of repairs possibly done without having to send the PC to a service center by 2025.  \\n  \\nThe Lenovo ThinkPad T14 Gen 5 shows that repairable design doesn’t need to be a niche that comes with uncomfortable trade-offs, but can be made possible within the requirements of a modern business laptop. We believe that [the future is repairable](https://www.ifixit.com/about-us) , and with this laptop, Lenovo makes a commitment to make this future a reality. We’re here for it.\\nLearn more about our collaboration from our [Lenovo Repair Hub](https://www.ifixit.com/collaborations/lenovo) . And if you have a Lenovo ThinkPad that’s in need of a repair, make sure to check out our [guides](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Lenovo_Thinkpad) and [parts](https://www.ifixit.com/Parts/Lenovo_Laptop) selection!\\n\\nRelated Stories\\n\\nFairphone 4 battery removal Repairability ### Going for Gold—Creating iFixit’s Gold Standard of Repair\\n\\ngreenpeace electronics chart iFixit ### Announcing iFixit Repairability Consulting\\n\\niFixit ### New Smartphone Repairability List\\n\\n### 1 Comment\\n\\nAdd Comment\\n\\nHey I have a laptop Lenovo IdeaPad 3 how run to a problem, when i turn on it he run on but not display the screen it plaque but I see and hear the moteur it run even th white light on the botton of power it light.\\n\\nManirakiza datus saint valdo\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v1.3\",\n      \"title\": \"Repairability Scoring Rubric v1.3 - iFixit\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* Edit\\n* Options\\n\\n* History\\n\\n# Repairability Scoring Rubric v1.3\\n\\nHere you'll find a summary of the various criteria considered when calculating iFixit repairability scores under scorecard version 1.3.\\n\\n**Scoring Factors**\\n\\n| |Weight |Note |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n|Design for Repair |90% |_Ease of disassembly/reassembly_ |\\n|Service Manual (if any) |10% |_Free, public, available via OEM support site_ |\\n\\n**Factors Not Considered**\\n\\n|Parts Availability |_Replacement parts available for purchase from the OEM at reasonable cost to end users will be a requirement in a future scorecard update._ |\\n| --- | --- |\\n|Parts Pairing |_Where common repairs are inhibited by parts pairing or calibration issues (e.g. full or partial loss of function, authenticity warnings, etc.) for which the OEM provides no freely available software-based remedy, penalties may be included in a future version of the scoring model._ |\\n|Unique Product Identifier |_In a future scorecard update, maximum points may be reserved for devices which can be readily identified (model number, service tag, etc.) in a non-working condition, making it straightforward to find compatible parts and instructions._ |\\n|Software Updates |_Duration of software updates may be included in a future version of the scorecard._ |\\n\\n**Revisions from v1.2**\\n\\n|Laptop Priority Part Modularity |_Refined scoring model for laptops, where disassembly/reassembly proxy times specific to I/O ports repair procedures are replaced with a simple modularity score._ |\\n| --- | --- |\\n\\n**Summary of Revisions**\\n\\nBlock Image\\n\\n**Reference**\\n\\n* [How iFixit Scores Repairability](https://www.ifixit.com/News/75533/how-ifixit-scores-repairability)\\n* Provisional Scoring Explained\\n* [Smartphone Repairability Index](https://www.ifixit.com/smartphone-repairability)\\n\\n### Author\\n\\n#### Jeff Suovanen\\n\\nMember since: 08/06/13\\n\\n453,173 Reputation\\n\\n259 Guides authored\\n\\nBadges: 49\\n\\n*\\n* \\n* \\n\\n\\\\+46 more badges\\n\\n### Team\\n\\n#### iFixit Member of iFixit\\n\\nStaff\\n\\n122 Members\\n\\n26,591 Guides authored\\n\\n### 0 Comments\\n\\nAdd Comment\\n\\n#### Add Comment\\n\\nCancel Post comment\\n\\n**View Statistics:**\\n\\nPast 24 Hours: 2\\n\\nPast 7 Days: 11\\n\\nPast 30 Days: 38\\n\\nAll Time: 1,870\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": null,\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"session_id\": \"ses_0d4353ddcffeFq8arVu83Zg8uc\"\n}",
