      "type": "thought",
      "text": "I have some information about iFixit scoring rubric. I need to find the specific iFixit repairability score for the user's laptop model. The user has an i5-7300HQ CPU, but I don't know the exact laptop model. I need to ask them to run PowerShell commands to get the model.\n\nI'll provide a PowerShell command to get the system model and manufacturer. Then I can search iFixit for that model.\n\nBut I can also search for common laptops with i5-7300HQ. However, the user wants the exact model. I'll guide them to run the command.\n\nNow, I need to provide a root cause analysis. WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR can be due to:\n\n1. CPU overheating\n2. CPU voltage instability (undervolting/overvolting)\n3. RAM failure\n4. Motherboard issues\n5. Storage device errors\n6. Driver issues (though less likely)\n\nI'll guide them to check Event Viewer for WHEA errors. Provide PowerShell command to extract events.\n\nAlso, provide a Python script to monitor temperatures using `wmi` and `psutil`. I'll write a simple script.\n\nNow, I need to keep my response concise but detailed. I'll structure as:\n\n1. PowerShell commands to get laptop model.\n2. PowerShell commands to extract WHEA errors.\n3. Root cause analysis.\n4. iFixit score estimate (once model known).\n5. Temperature monitoring Python script.\n\nLet's start.",
