    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "websearch",
      "code": "{\"query\": \"\\\"HP OMEN 15-ce0xx\\\" iFixit\", \"numResults\": 5}",
      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_bd93a2e2b7794e10903634cbfb24fd6b\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/Guide/HP+Omen+15-CE0XX+Fan+Replacement/157629\",\n      \"title\": \"HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement - iFixit Repair Guide\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2024-10-24\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Free Shipping on Domestic Orders $75+\\n\\n# HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement\\n\\n## Introduction\\n\\nThis guide will walk you through the process of replacing a faulty ventilation fan in your _HP Omen 15-CE0XX_ laptop. A malfunctioning fan can cause overheating and system instability, leading to potential permanent damage to your device. It is important to take appropriate precautions before beginning the fan replacement process to ensure a successful outcome.\\n\\nBefore starting, make sure to _power down_ your laptop completely and _disconnect_ from any external power source. It is recommended to _back up your data_ and review any troubleshooting steps to ensure that the fan is indeed the root cause of the issue.\\n\\nThroughout the process, you will need basic tools such as _screwdrivers_ , _prying tools_ and a _replacement fan_ that is compatible with the _HP Omen 15-CE0XX_ . You should follow the instructions closely and handle the internal components with care to avoid any damage.\\nOnce you have completed the fan replacement, it is important to test your laptop to ensure that it is running correctly and without overheating. This guide is intended for individuals with basic technical skills, but if you are unsure or not confident in your abilities, it is always best to seek professional assistance\\n\\n## What you need\\n\\n* ## **Step 1** Fan\\n  \\n  HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement, Fan: step 1, image 1 of 1\\n  \\n    + Use a Phillips #0 screwdriver to remove the eight 5.5 mm screws from the bottom cover.\\n    + Use a Phillips #0 screwdriver to remove the two 10 (?) mm screws from the bottom cover.\\n  \\n  Edit\\n  \\n  Ask FixBot Add a comment\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  #### Add Comment\\n  \\n  Cancel Post comment\\n* ## **Step 2**\\n  \\n  HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement: step 2, image 1 of 2\\n  \\n+ Use a plastic opening tool to gently separate the bottom cover from the main chassis, and pull the cover upwards.\\n  \\n  Edit\\n  \\n  Ask FixBot Add a comment\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  #### Add Comment\\nCancel Post comment\\n* ## **Step 3**\\n  \\n    + Unscrew the four 5.5 mm screws that connect the battery to the main system, and gently detach the battery.\\n    + While removing, make sure to avoid pulling the battery straight out. Instead gently lift the lower half of the battery and slide it away from the motherboard in an away and upwards motion.\\n  \\n  Edit\\n  \\n  Ask FixBot Add a comment\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  #### Add Comment\\n  \\n  Cancel Post comment\\n* \\n* ## **Step 4**\\n  \\n+ Remove the trunk outlet for the replacement fan. This is done by unscrewing the three 5.5mm screws on the trunk outlet and then sliding it outwards to remove.\\n  \\n  Edit\\n  \\n  Ask FixBot Add a comment\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  #### Add Comment\\n  \\n  Cancel Post comment\\n* ## **Step 5**\\n  \\n    + Use a Phillips #00 screwdriver to unscrew the five 5.5 mm screws that secure the bracket to the frame.\\n    + After all screws are loose, gently lift the bracket upwards.\\n+ Be careful with the power cable sitting right under this bracket. You might have to move the cable around gently to get the bracket out\\n  \\n  Edit\\n  \\n  Ask FixBot Add a comment\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  #### Add Comment\\n  \\n  Cancel Post comment\\n* ## **Step 6**\\n  \\n    + Disconnect the fan cable from the motherboard using a plastic opening/ pry tool.\\n    + Do not use too much force while pulling the fan cable as it may break. If required, you may use a secondary plastic opening/pry tool for support.\\n  \\n  Edit\\n  \\n  Ask FixBot Add a comment\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  #### Add Comment\\n  \\n  Cancel Post comment\\n* ## **Step 7**\\n  \\n    + Carefully pull the fan out, clean the dust if required.\\n    + Finally, you can now replace the faulty fan with the new fan by following the above steps in reverse order.\\n  \\n  Edit\\n  \\n  Ask FixBot Add a comment\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  #### Add Comment\\n  \\n  Cancel Post comment\\n\\nConclusion\\n\\nTo reassemble your device, follow these instructions in reverse order.\\nGive the author +30 points! You're Finished!\\n\\nCancel: I did not complete this guide.\\n\\nOne other person completed this guide.\\n\\n### Author\\n\\nwith 4 other contributors\\n\\n#### Nadim Patel\\n\\nMember since: 01/27/23\\n\\n154 Reputation\\n\\n1 Guide authored\\n\\nBadges: 4\\n\\n* \\n* \\n* \\n\\n\\\\+1 more badge\\n\\n### 0 Guide Comments\\n\\nAdd a comment\\n\\n#### Add Comment\\n\\nCancel Post comment\\n\\n**View Statistics:**\\n\\nPast 24 Hours: 3\\n\\nPast 7 Days: 38\\n\\nPast 30 Days: 125\\n\\nAll Time: 3,212\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/Device/HP_15_Series\",\n      \"title\": \"HP 15 Series Repair Help: Learn How to Fix It Yourself.\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Free Shipping on Domestic Orders $75+\\n\\nHP 15 Series\\n\\nTable of Contents\\n\\n* Background and Identification\\n* Additional Information\\n\\n* Edit\\n* Options\\n\\n* History\\n* \\n* Show Other Languages\\n\\nHP 15 Series\\n\\n# HP 15 Series Repair\\n\\nBudget 15\\\" laptop series released by HP.\\n\\nAuthor: Joseph Sctbunio (and 5 other contributors)\\n\\nCreate a Guide\\n\\n## Popular Forum Questions\\n\\nAsk a Question\\n\\n|3 Answers\\n\\n2 Score |### Laptop won't boot up, power light and charging light flash\\n\\nHP Notebook 15s-fq0000 Series |\\n| --- | --- |\\n|5 Answers\\n\\n9 Score |### My laptop won't turn on\\n\\nHP 15-D076NR |\\n|1 Answer\\n\\n0 Score |### What can I upgrade on my laptop?\\n\\nHP 15 Laptop (15-dy) |\\n|1 Answer\\n\\n0 Score |### My computer is black screen and won’t turn on!\\n\\nHP 15-e Series |\\n\\n## Background and Identification\\n\\nThe Hewlett-Packard (HP) Company, now succeeded by HP Inc., is an American multinational information technology (IT) company. HP Inc.\\nis headquartered in Palo Alto, California and primarily develops personal computers and printing related products, including 3D printing. In 2015, the computer and printing departments of the company separated from the rest of the Hewlett-Packard Company to form HP Inc. The Hewlett-Packard Company is now known as the Hewlett Packard Enterprise and oversees the business and enterprise operations of the Hewlett Packard brand.\\n\\nThe ‘15’ in the title refers to the size of the screen of the laptop series. HP laptops can generally be found in the following screen sizes: 13-inch, 15-inch, and 17-inch. As a result, this page will refer to repair documentation and information on HP laptops that include 15-inch sized screens.\\n\\nThe following lines of HP products are or have been produced with a 15-inch (15.6”) screen:\\n\\n* HP 15 Series\\n* HP Envy\\n* HP Pavilion\\n* HP Spectre x360\\n* HP Omen\\n* HP Chromebook\\n* HP EliteBook\\nThis page will cover service and repair information for all models of HP 15 series laptops. The HP 15 Series can be identified by the structure of the following: screen size and model number (ex: 15-ac121dx). The letter after the dash corresponds to various other submodels of the HP 15 Series. Surprisingly, the letters cover almost all letters of the alphabet other than h, i, l, m, o, q, s, t, v, x, y, z.\\n\\n## Additional Information\\n\\n[HP 15 Series Lineup](https://www.notebookcheck.net/HP-15-Series.124890.0.html)\\n\\n[HP Inc. Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HP_Inc.)\\n\\n[Amazon product page](https://www.amazon.com/slp/hp-pavilion-15-notebook-pc/ywrua4dk86g5x6q?tag=ifixitam-20)\\n\\n### Author\\n\\nwith 5 other contributors\\n\\n#### Joseph Sctbunio\\n\\nMember since: 09/23/17\\n\\n7,884 Reputation\\n\\n42 Guides authored\\n\\nBadges: 22\\n\\n* \\n* \\n* \\n\\n\\\\+19 more badges\\n\\n**View Statistics:**\\n\\nPast 24 Hours: 40\\n\\nPast 7 Days: 535\\n\\nPast 30 Days: 1,624\\n\\nAll Time: 107,724\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.manualslib.com/manual/900227/Hp-Omen-15.html\",\n      \"title\": \"HP OMEN 15 MAINTENANCE AND SERVICE MANUAL Pdf Download | ManualsLib\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2015-06-25\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"[ManualsLib](https://www.manualslib.com \\\"Manuals Library\\\")\\n\\n Upload\\n\\nDownload Table of Contents Contents\\n\\nAdd to my manuals\\n\\nDelete from my manuals\\n\\nShare\\n\\nURL of this page:\\n\\nHTML Link:\\n\\n* [Pinterest](https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.manualslib.com%2Fmanual%2F900227%2FHp-Omen-15.html&description=HP+OMEN+15+MAINTENANCE+AND+SERVICE+MANUAL+Pdf+Download&media=https%3A%2F%2Fstatic-data2.manualslib.com%2Fproduct-images%2F388%2F900227%2Fhp-omen-15-laptop.jpg)\\n\\nBookmark this page Add Manual will be automatically added to \\\"My Manuals\\\"\\n\\nPrint this page\\n\\nHP OMEN 15 Maintenance And Service Manual\\n\\n1. Manuals\\n2. Brands\\n3. HP Manuals\\n4. Laptop\\n5. OMEN 15\\n6. Maintenance and service manual\\n\\n# HP OMEN 15 Maintenance And Service Manual\\n\\nHide thumbs Also See for OMEN 15 :\\n\\n* Product end-of-life disassembly instructions (8 pages)\\n\\n* page of 67 Go\\n  \\n  / 67\\n* Contents\\n* Table of Contents\\n* Bookmarks\\n\\n#### Related Manuals for HP OMEN 15\\n\\n*\\nLaptop HP OMEN 15 Product End-Of-Life Disassembly Instructions\\n  \\n  External options (8 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP OMEN 17 Product End-Of-Life Disassembly Instructions\\n  \\n  External options (6 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP OMEN 17 Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  (86 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP OMEN 16 Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  (89 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP 16-b0 Series Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  (90 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP OMEN 16 inch Gaming Laptop PC Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  (109 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP OMEN Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  (78 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP OMEN Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  Model numbers 15-ce000 through 15-ce099 (112 pages)\\n\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP OMEN Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  15 series laptop pc (102 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP OMEN Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  15 laptop pc (95 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP OMEN Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  17 laptop pc (98 pages)\\n*\\nLaptop HP OMEN Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  (101 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP Omen Setup Instructions\\n  \\n  (15 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP OMEN MAX Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  16 inch gaming laptop pc (111 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP Omen series Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  (96 pages)\\n* \\n  \\n  Laptop HP OMEN X Maintenance And Service Manual\\n  \\n  Laptop pc (86 pages)\\n\\n#### Summary of Contents for HP OMEN 15\\n\\n* Page 1 HP OMEN Notebook PC 15 Maintenance and Service Guide IMPORTANT! This document is intended for HP authorized service providers only.\\n* Page 2 SD Logo is a trademark of its proprietor. The information contained herein is subject to change without notice. The only warranties for HP products and services are set forth in the express warranty statements accompanying such products and services. Nothing herein should be construed as constituting an additional warranty.\\n* Page 3 Safety warning notice WARNING!\\n\\n...\\n\\n0 ports AC Smart Pin adapter plug Keyboard/pointing devices Full size Dura Coat island-style keyboard Touchpad requirements: ●...\\n* ### Page 9: Getting To Know Your Computer\\n  \\n  Select System and Security, select System, and then click Device Manager in the left column. A list displays all the devices installed on your computer. –or– From the Start screen, type hp performance advisor, and then select HP Performance Advisor. –or– From the Windows desktop, click the HP OMEN Central Ops icon on the taskbar, and then click HP Performance Advisor.\\n* ### Page 10: Display\\n  \\n  For wireless regulatory notices, see the section of the Regulatory, Safety, and Environmental Notices that applies to your country or region. To access this guide, from the Start screen, type support, and then select the HP Support Assistant app.\\n* ### Page 11: Right Side\\n  \\n  Right side Component Description Memory card reader Reads optional memory cards that store, manage, share, or access information.\\nTo insert a card: Hold the card label-side up, with connectors facing the slot, insert the card into the slot, and then press in on the card until it is firmly seated.\\n* ### Page 12: Rear\\n  \\n  For additional safety information, refer to the Regulatory, Safety, and Environmental Notices. To access this guide, from the Start screen, type support, and then select the HP Support Assistant app. NOTE: When a device is connected to the jack, the computer speakers are disabled.\\n* ### Page 13: Top\\n  \\n  Touchpad Component Description Touchpad zone Reads your finger gestures to move the pointer or activate items on the screen. TIP: You can disable the touchpad or change the touchpad sensitivity and click speed. Left touchpad button Functions like the left button on an external mouse. Right touchpad button Functions like the right button on an external mouse.\\n* Page 14 Lights TIP: You can customize the keyboard lighting. Component Description ● Power light On: The computer is on.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/Device/HP_OMEN_15_Series\",\n      \"title\": \"HP OMEN 15 Series Help: Learn How to Fix It Yourself.\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Free Shipping on Domestic Orders $75+\\n\\nHP OMEN 15 Series\\n\\n* Edit\\n*